# üìö Interactive PDF Reader with LangChain & Streamlit

This web application allows you to upload a PDF and ask it questions using a built-in AI assistant. It extracts relevant information from the document using advanced NLP techniques and displays both the chatbot's response and the original PDF content side by side for full context.

---

## üöÄ Features

- Upload any PDF document
- Ask natural language questions about the content
- View referenced pages from the document next to the chatbot
- Built with:
  - [Streamlit](https://streamlit.io) for the frontend
  - [LangChain](https://www.langchain.com/) for the RAG pipeline
  - [OpenAI GPT-4o](https://platform.openai.com/) for language generation
  - [Hugging Face](https://huggingface.co/sentence-transformers) for embeddings
  - [PyMuPDF](https://pymupdf.readthedocs.io/) for page previews

---

## üõ†Ô∏è Setup Instructions

1. **Clone the repo**
```bash
git clone https://github.com/Sathvikaallenki/interactive-pdf-reader.git
cd interactive-pdf-reader 

2. **Install dependencies**
pip install -r requirements.txt
3. **Configure your environment variables Create a .env file in the root directory:** 

OPENAI_API_KEY=your-openai-api-key 
4. **Run the app** 

    python -m streamlit run app.py
